reviews.text: My wife and I were looking for a place to enjoy an early dinner as we were preparing to fly out from Hong Kong to San Francisco the next morning.  When we arrived at the Curry Lounge, the manager was very nice and careful not to rush us, but told us the kitchen was about to close for an hour to prep for dinner service but if we would like to order they would accommodate us.  Again, he was very polite, but I could tell he was also concerned about aggravating his kitchen staff.  I was a little worried what kind of quality food we would get under the circumstances, but I needn't have been.  Both of our meals were served hot and delicious! The barman and the manager/host/waiter were both perfectly attentive, friendly and courteous.

Best food in this area I had so far. The staffs are very nice and helpful that they’d love to chat with you and refill your water. 

We waited around 30 minutes for our food but here was so many people at the restaurant. It may not be a good idea for super hungry people, but I have to say their food is amazing. 

Their shrimp is perfectly grilled, and marinated perfectly. My favourite dish is their tandoori chicken, it’s so tender and full of flavour.
Not worth the price. Food is expensive and taste below average. 4 of us on the table and they served only 2 glasses of water that too on asking for it.

Been coming to curry lounge for a couple years now, the food is really very good and the service is excellent as expected in Tung Chung. This small restaurant recently had a make over and now seats 100 covers! With a great bar and wonderful cocktails, I love coming back here often. 5 star rating for a 5 star esablishment.

Unprofessional service, the people who handle guests are just not trained formally and it's quite visible.Ambience , good chefs will always change , but the culture of people who serve remains.I must appreciate, but be vocal on bad clueless service. Extremely disappointed with the way guests are treated.
